-- Belka Sees Turbulence From Euro Zone as Biggest Threat to Poland's Economy
-- B y   N a t h a n i e l   E s p i n o
-- 2010-12-30T06:59:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-30/belka-sees-turbulence-from-euro-zone-as-biggest-threat-to-poland-s-economy.html
Market “turbulence” caused by
crises among the countries that use the euro currency is the
main threat to Poland’s economy, central bank Governor Marek
Belka said today in an interview on Radio Tok FM, adding that he
predicts the zloty currency will strengthen.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nathaniel Espino at 
 nespino@bloomberg.net  